Franchise Coordinator
Mobilink GSM (PMCL)
-
Lahore
The ideal candidate should:
Hold at least a Bachelors in Business administration.
Have 2 to 4 years of relevant work experience.
Job Description
Create and analyze the weekly/ monthly reports.
Coordinate with other departments (Sale and Support Centers etc.) for follow-ups.
Analyze performance evaluation of all franchises, MSPs and BDOs of the region and guiding FSEs on improvement needs.
Coordinate with QAST/FSEs for required training material for franchise CCRs and arrange need based training sessions where required.
Arrange training sessions for franchise CCRs (Level I, II III certification, bi-monthly snaps etc.) as per franchise support calendar.
Provide backup to FSEs in such a way that FC handles workload of the FSE who is unavailable (on leave) and provide support to FSEs during visits.
Generate need based reports and data collection from business centers, franchise, and MSP and business development officers.
Essential Skills
Strong communication and interpersonal skills
Effective follow-up skills
Proficiency in MS Office Suite
Desirable Skills
Good analytical skills
Pleasant and presentable personality
LUMS
